# Cloudflare Pages, redirects
# Format: <from> <to> <status>
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# IMPORTANT: Cloudflare Pages matches `_redirects` SOURCES on the PATH ONLY,
# never the host or scheme. A host-based source like
# `https://www.najdorfesports.gg/*` never matches a real request path, so it
# silently does nothing (a path-only apex rule would also just loop). Host
# redirects therefore live as Cloudflare zone-level Single Redirects in the
# dashboard, NOT in this file:
#   - www -> apex: Single Redirect on the najdorfesports.gg zone
#     (match `https://www.*`, target `https://${1}`, 301). Verified live:
#     www/ and www/<path>?<query> 301 to the apex with path + query preserved.
# `najdorfesports.pages.dev` still serves 200 (it cannot be redirected from
# this zone), but every page's <link rel="canonical"> points at the apex, so
# search engines treat the apex as canonical. Do NOT re-add a
# `https://.../*` source line here: it is dead weight.

# News slug rename: the launch announcement moved off the "rebrand" slug
# (the org acquired the Rankers roster, it is not a rebrand) to an
# acquisition slug. Preserve any inbound links to the old URL in all locales.
/news/2026-05-najdorf-rebrand/        /news/2026-05-najdorf-acquires-rankers/        301
/zh-TW/news/2026-05-najdorf-rebrand/  /zh-TW/news/2026-05-najdorf-acquires-rankers/  301
/zh-CN/news/2026-05-najdorf-rebrand/  /zh-CN/news/2026-05-najdorf-acquires-rankers/  301

# Locale prefixes are case-sensitive on disk (Astro builds /zh-TW/ and
# /zh-CN/), but URL-bar autocomplete and hand-typed URLs love to lowercase
# the path. Forward the lowercase variants so they don't 404.
/zh-tw/*  /zh-TW/:splat  301
/zh-tw    /zh-TW/        301
/zh-cn/*  /zh-CN/:splat  301
/zh-cn    /zh-CN/        301
